# Regenerable data
data/repos/
data/snapshots/
data/cache/*
# ...but keep the screenshot manifest: export-web's image re-tag needs it, and
# the daily CI job has no other way to recover it (the PNGs it maps are committed
# under docs/images/, but this manifest is what ties them to each row + its dims).
!data/cache/image_manifest.json
# ...and the MAD CSV (arcade rotation/players/controls): committed so a failed
# daily fetch falls back to the last good copy instead of publishing a
# data.json with the arcade metadata columns wiped.
!data/cache/ArcadeDatabase.csv
# ...and catver.ini (arcade genres, AntoPISA's current-MAME copy): committed so
# a failed daily fetch falls back to the last good copy instead of publishing a
# data.json with the Genre column wiped.
!data/cache/catver.ini
# ...and the derived MAME metadata (setname → year/manufacturer/parent/desc):
# the raw 71 MB DAT stays local, but this 0.5 MB gz gives the daily CI build the
# same data, so arcade year/manufacturer/genre fill on the live site too.
!data/cache/mame_meta.json.gz
# ...and the derived mame2003-plus specs (rotation/players/controls per setname):
# provisional gray-fill for arcade rows the curated Arcade Database hasn't
# reached yet; committed so the daily build works even if the fetch fails.
!data/cache/mame2003_specs.json.gz
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Keep the db and exports? They're regenerable but useful to commit for history.
# Uncomment to ignore:
# data/misterzine.sqlite
# data/exports/

# Claude Code local state
.claude/

# MacOS
.DS_Store
